column5: Better weather at the Perch Fest today in Orillia, caught some nice keepers but not tagged for me yet this year, had one last year.  I also caught what has to be the Tinniest Perch ever!
The smallest fish is just as hard to catch as the biggest haha. Would have been a nice day to fish today!
Couple of nice fatties and a nice little baby!
Long as your having fun!,lol,that's all that matters.  .
Are you sure you didn't place an ad on KIJIJI for those 2 fish?
I'm looking at going back this thursday early morning for some perch fishing.
Come on. The sun is shining, the water is calm and only 2 layers of clothes, that is not spring perch fishin' weather.  Nice to get out in the boat again I bet.

Some of my first Fishing memories as a kid were from the Orillia Perch Festival. Always a Good time! Props to the city of Orillia and organizers for the continued success of the derby and for being a Fisherman friendly city! <><
Well, except for the fact that they closed one launch, and the one that's open only has one side right now... there's also a lot less parking for trucks and trailers.
I'm going up tomorrow morning, anyone want to go?
We caught 1 tag on Tuesday, buddys name Bob, on the wall. Fishing was great yesterday. I think were heading back up Tesday for 3 days.
Nice going fish farmer, going to be nice out this weekend!
